## Examples

### Good Citation Example

```markdown
## Niche Narrative

Startups value solutions that work on day one [^1]. The market shows a 30-50% increase in efficiency when using design systems [^2].

## Sources & Citations

[^1]: Moreno Celta, R. (2025). *Design System Trends*. Design Systems Collective. - https://example.com/article
[^2]: Autentika. (2024, June 18). *Design System Efficiency Study*. - https://example.com/study
```

### Bad Citation Example

```markdown
## Niche Narrative

Startups value solutions that work on day one. The market shows a 30-50% increase in efficiency.

<!-- No citations! This is not allowed. -->
```

## Summary

1. **All AI-generated content must include citations** - No exceptions
2. **Citation format**: `[^number]` footnotes with sources section
3. **Parser utility**: Use `manus-parser.ts` for parsing and formatting
4. **Quality gates**: Validate citations before using outputs
5. **Enforcement**: Agents must request, parse, and include citations
6. **Trust through transparency**: Every claim must be traceable

**No AI-generated content is complete without proper citations and source attribution.**
